snippet.title: Most famous Bob Saget Quotes, thought and saying you need to listen
snippet.description:
Most famous Bob Saget Quotes, thought and saying you need to listen 

Bob Saget, American stand-up comedian.

Robert Lane Saget was an American stand-up comedian, actor, and television host. His acting roles included Danny Tanner on the ABC sitcom Full House, its Netflix sequel Fuller House, and the voice of narrator Ted Mosby on the CBS sitcom How I Met Your Mother.

List of all bob saget Quotes, thought and saying below

1. “I become a chameleon for wherever I am.” 

2. “I had enough therapy to know when I broke it down, it became clearer to me: Yes, comedy was kind of a cleansing thing for me to do.” 

3. “I think when you dissect a joke too much, you have ruined whatever there is in comedy.” 

4. “The nature of comedy is ‘just do it.’” 

5. “I have nine compartments in my brain, and four of them don’t stop.” 

6. “I really love making people laugh.” 

7. “I never expected to live this long.” 

8. “My confidence wavers between being genuine and being insecure.”

9. “When you’re famous, you’re always famous. It doesn’t go away.” 

10. “I don’t censor myself, but I don’t want to force my sick-skewed version of the world, either.”

11. “Celebrity is a word that I find offensive. That’s the c-word. I hate it. It means no discernible talent, It means all you want is to be famous. It doesn’t mean you’re a writer, an actor, or a mime. I think I wanna not to be a celebrity.” 

12. “I was so depressed for so many years over trying to become a working comedian that my sense of self-worth would plummet.” 

13. “Like with any good art form, if you can entertain people and make them think, it’s an honor. It’s just an honor to be a comedian.”

14. "I had enough therapy to know when I broke it down, it became clearer to me: Yes, comedy was kind of a cleansing thing for me to do."

15. "Soon, I'm going to meet somebody around my own age, and she's going to be smart and beautiful, and I'm going to date her daughter."

16. "It's interesting to talk to young comedians. I love it because it makes me go, 'Oh, that's how I can be funny."

17. "It's still a soft R, but when I watch other people's standup, I'm dumbfounded that people call me dirty. That's only because I did family television."

18. "I really love standup because it's something that I've been literally doing for 40 years, which means I'm a thousand years old."

19. "I don't like the negative of reality tv - the 'you're no good, so you have to leave, I choose you, but I thought you really loved me.' It's all about how bad people are and I just hate that. I like Pimp my Ride where someone is helping somebody."

I hope you liked the above Bob Saget Quotes. Don’t forget to mention the best line that you liked most from the above lines in the comment box below.

If you like this type of videos don't forget to subscribe ❤ 

As always your feedback is welcome.
